            <biogHist>
                <p>Hector MacLeod was born c. 1792 to Alexander MacLeod, a farmer, and Marion
                    MacLeod née Johnstone. He was single and a shoemaker, and at the time of the
                    1841 census his mother was staying with him at Driomore. By 1861 he was applying
                    his trade in Clachan from a large house with two windows. By 1871 he had moved
                    to Linique and had become a dealer in eggs. He died in June 1872 from general
                    debility and his nephew Neil MacLeod signed the death certificate.</p>
                <p>Carmichael collected a poem beginning 'Gair nan cath eir tulach shamhna' from
                    MacLeod.</p>
